{"comment": "The squareRoot function determines if a span of List objects is a palindrome. Since the List struct inherits from a variant of five monostate alternatives, its equality depends only on which variant index is active. The provided test cases cover the empty span, single-element spans, matching and mismatched pairs, and longer palindromic and non-palindromic sequences.", "tests": ["squareRootv(std::vector<List>{})", "squareRootv(std::vector<List>{List(std::in_place_index<List::A>)})", "squareRootv(std::vector<List>{List(std::in_place_index<List::A>),List(std::in_place_index<List::A>)})", "squareRootv(std::vector<List>{List(std::in_place_index<List::A>),List(std::in_place_index<List::E>)})", "squareRootv(std::vector<List>{List(std::in_place_index<List::A>),List(std::in_place_index<List::E>),List(std::in_place_index<List::A>)})", "squareRootv(std::vector<List>{List(std::in_place_index<List::A>),List(std::in_place_index<List::E>),List(std::in_place_index<List::I>)})", "squareRootv(std::vector<List>{List(std::in_place_index<List::O>),List(std::in_place_index<List::U>),List(std::in_place_index<List::U>),List(std::in_place_index<List::O>)})", "squareRootv(std::vector<List>{List(std::in_place_index<List::O>),List(std::in_place_index<List::U>),List(std::in_place_index<List::I>),List(std::in_place_index<List::O>)})"]}
